[[File:Rökstenen och riksantikvarie Hans Hildebrand 1890.jpg|thumb|Hans Hildebrand sitting by the [[Rök Runestone]]]]
'''Hans Olof Hildebrand Hildebrand''' (5 April 1842 in [[Stockholm]] – 2 February 1913) was a Swedish archeologist. Born in Stockholm, he was the son of [[Bror Emil Hildebrand]] and Anna Mathilda Ekecrantz. He was the brother of Emil Hildebrand, and in 1867 married Elin Maria Charlotta Martin. <ref>[https://www.geni.com/people/Hans-Olof-Hildebrand/6000000012614286609 Hans Olof Hildebrand]</ref><ref name=hans>{{cite encyclopedia|last=Hildebrand|first=Bengt|title =Hans O H Hildebrand|encyclopedia =[[Svenskt biografiskt lexikon]]|year=1971–1973|publisher=[[National Archives of Sweden]]|location =Stockholm |language=Swedish|volume=19|page=43|url =https://sok.riksarkivet.se/SBL/Presentation.aspx?id=13584|accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref> 

Hildebrand, along with his father and his colleague [[Oscar Montelius]], is considered one of the fathers of Swedish archaeology. He worked both in [[archaeology]] and [[numismatics]], mainly of the High and Late [[Middle Ages]]. He is internationally known as one of the pioneers of the archaeological technique of [[typology (archaeology)|typology]].<ref name="hans" />

Between 1895 and his death, Hildebrand was Director-General of the [[Swedish Academy]]. From 1879-1907 he was also Secretary to the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Letters, History and Antiquities]] and Custodian of the National Heritage, ''[[riksantikvarie]]''. Whilst at the Academy of Letters he contributed to the foundation of the journal ''[[Fornvännen]]''. He was a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]] from 1891.<ref name="hans" /> He gave the [[Rhind Lectures]] in 1896, on "Industrial arts of Scandinavia in pagan times".<ref name="listing">{{cite web|url=http://www.socantscot.org/content/documents/public_rhind_lecturers_list.doc|title=List of 133 Lecturers|work=The Rhind Lectures|publisher=[[Society of Antiquaries of Scotland]]|accessdate=27 November 2010| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722055840/http://www.socantscot.org/content/documents/public_rhind_lecturers_list.doc| archivedate=July 22, 2011 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | url=https://archive.org/details/industrialartsof00hild | title=The industrial arts of Scandinavia in the pagan time | publisher=Pub. for the Committee of Council on Education by [[Chapman & Hall]] | author=Hildebrand, Hans | year=1883 | location=London}}</ref>

