'''Norwegian Institute of Local History''' ({{lang-no|Norsk lokalhistorisk institutt}}) is an agency under the [[Norwegian Ministry of Culture and Church Affairs]]. It was established in 1955. Its purposes are to "encourage and promote local and regional history" in Norway and to "stimulate a high professional and pedagogical level of research in local history". The current director is [[Knut Sprauten]].<ref name=institute>{{cite web|url=http://www.lokalhistorie.no/nli/english.html|title=The Norwegian Institute of Local History|publisher=Norwegian Institute of Local History|accessdate=11 March 2009}}</ref>
It runs the website Lokalhistorie.no, and publishes the periodical ''Lokalhistorisk magasin'' in cooperation with the National Federation of Local History Associations.<ref name=institute/>
